Britain and Ireland Trig Pillars Map

This is a map of the OS trig pillars in Britain and Ireland, sourced from TrigpointingUK. Use the layers control to filter which condition(s) of trig you wish to see. The categories are fairly self explanatory - my reading of "Converted" is that it was a pillar that has been converted to a different type of survey monument, e.g. a buried block.
Condition Key: Good, Moved, Slightly Damaged; Unreachable but visible, Damaged, Toppled; Remains, Possibly missing; Destroyed, Converted, Not logged, Unknown
